                        <condition>Ruth J. Dean notes that the manuscript is a palimpsest, with fragments of early English letter-forms discernible, written in a round script that is suggestive of the tenth century. 
                           Prickings for the original ruling are still visible, with the page rotated so that the erased text and the new text are at right angles to each other
                           ('Manuscripts of St Elizabeth of Schönau in England', <title>Modern Language Review</title>, 32 [1937], p. 63)
